        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 6:47PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 645 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Wolf Creek, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and brief heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Cascade, Wolf Creek, Bowmans Corner, Tower Rock State Park, and
Craig.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
